data.title: Gran Tierra Energy Inc. posted Q3 results, with exploration success in Ecuador. Financials and operations discussed in USD.
data.description: Gran Tierra Energy Inc. disclosed its financial and operational results for the quarter ending on September 30, 2025. The numbers were reported in United States dollars, with production volumes being provided on an average working interest before royalties basis. The company operates under the tickers NYSE American: GTE, TSX: GTE, and LSE: GTE. Production is measured in barrels of oil equivalent per day (boepd or boe/d), based on WI sales before royalties. For a detailed breakdown of per barrel amounts based on net after royalty production, interested parties can refer to Gran Tierra's Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q filed on October 30, 2025.

data.title: CFAS is launched with 40+ leaders to operationalize AI in national security, incl. NVIDIA, Google, OpenAI, AWS.
data.description: Over 40 prominent figures from government, industry, and academia, including NVIDIA, Google, OpenAI, and AWS, gathered at the launch of the Center for Frontier AI Security in Arlington, Virginia on October 30, 2025. This initiative aims to translate policy into practical strategies for leveraging AI in enhancing national security measures. This collaboration signifies a significant step towards bridging the gap between theoretical frameworks and real-world applications in the field of AI security.

data.title: NextDecade gives update on Q3-Q4 2025: finalized financing, achieved positive FIDs for Train 4 & Train 5.
data.description: Houston-based NextDecade Corporation announced their latest updates for the third quarter 2025 and early fourth quarter 2025. The company, listed as NEXT on the NASDAQ, shared significant milestones including successful financing and Final Investment Decisions (FIDs) for Rio Grande LNG Train 4 and Train 5. CEO Matt Schatzman expressed optimism, stating that these recent developments have been transformative for NextDecade by ensuring financial progress while avoiding dilution to company shares.

data.title: Ramaco Resources signs CRADA with DOE's NETL on rare earth minerals. Important dates: Oct. 30, 2025. Stock: NASDAQ: METC, METCB.
data.description: In Lexington, Kentucky on October 30, 2025, Ramaco Resources, Inc. (NASDAQ: METC, METCB) has disclosed a significant partnership. This collaboration marks a key milestone for Ramaco in its efforts to advance energy research.

data.title: Knight Therapeutics launches JORNAY PM™ in Canada, extended-release methylphenidate for ADHD in children 6-12.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, Knight Therapeutics Inc. introduced JORNAY PM™ (methylphenidate HCI extended-release capsules) in Canada. This product, designed for children aged 6 to 12 with Attention-Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD), offers an extended-release formulation of methylphenidate, a stimulant medication. Knight Therapeutics Inc., listed as TSX: GUD, serves as a pan-American (excluding USA) specialty pharmaceutical company.

data.title: Toromont reports Q3 2025 results: Revenue $1.31B (-2%), Net Earnings $140.6M (+7%). Quarterly dividend of $0.52 approved.
data.description: Toromont Industries Ltd. reported their financial results for Q3 2025. Revenue decreased by 2% to $1,314.9 million, with operating income increasing by 8% to $189.5 million. Net earnings rose by 7% to $140.6 million, and basic EPS increased by 8% to $1.73. The Equipment Group revenue declined by 4%, while CIMCO revenue increased by 22%. For the nine months ended September 30, 2025, revenue was up 2% to $3.8 billion. Operating income stayed the same at $458.8 million. Net earnings decreased by 3% to $339.4 million, with a basic EPS of $4.18. Bookings for Q3 rose by 47%, totaling $548.8 million, and backlog was $1.3 billion as of Sept 30, 2025. Toromont's share price was $154.52 with a market cap of $12.6 billion. The net debt to total capitalization ratio was -9% in Sept 2025. The company also canceled 337,500 common shares in the first nine months of 2025.

data.title: Apple stock reaches all-time high post Q4 earnings beat, revenue of $102.47B, with $1.85 EPS, beating analyst estimates. Sales: Americas $44.19B, Europe $28.7B, Greater China $14.49B, Japan $6.64B, Asia Pacific $8.44B. Total revenue up 8% YoY, EPS climbed 13% YoY.
data.description: Apple Inc reported their fiscal fourth-quarter revenue as $102.47 billion, surpassing analyst estimates of $102.17 billion. The company's earnings per share were $1.85, beating the estimated $1.76 per share. Apple has consistently exceeded analyst expectations for 11 consecutive quarters. Year-over-year, total revenue increased by 8% and earnings per share rose by 13%. In terms of regional sales, Americas generated $44.19 billion, Europe $28.7 billion, Greater China $14.49 billion, Japan $6.64 billion, and the rest of Asia Pacific $8.44 billion. The full article can be accessed on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Buddha Board launches sweepstakes to gift 1000 boards to educators for mental health; 40 educators to receive 25 boards.
data.description: In an initiative to support educators focusing on enhancing students' mental health, Buddha Board plans to donate 1000 of their products. Taking place in Vancouver, BC, this October, the company is set to distribute 25 Buddha Boards to 40 educators, totaling to 1000 boards, free of charge. This gesture aims to aid educators in their mission to positively impact the well-being of their students.

data.title: LiveOnNY's Second Annual Donor Heroes 5K in NYC united hundreds to support organ donation, honoring donors and families.
data.description: In New York on October 30, 2025, the Second Annual Donor Heroes 5K was organized by LiveOnNY at Flushing Meadows Corona Park, attracting hundreds of attendees. The event served as a platform to commemorate, appreciate, and inspire, specifically recognizing organ, eye, and tissue donors along with their families.

data.title: NewMarket Corporation raises quarterly dividend to $3.00 per share, 9% increase from prior dividend of $2.75. Payable Jan 2, 2026.
data.description: In Richmond, VA, the Board of Directors of NewMarket Corporation (NYSE: NEU) announced a quarterly dividend of $3.00 per share on its common stock, marking a $0.25 increase from the previous $2.75 per share dividend. This raise signifies a nearly 9% uptick in the dividend amount. The dividend is set to be distributed on January 2, 2026, to shareholders of record as of December 15, 2025.

data.title: National thought leader Rich Harwood will speak at Frederick CivicCon on November 11 at 6:30pm at Hood College.
data.description: In Frederick, Maryland, a collaboration between Frederick CivicCon and Hood College will feature renowned thought leader Rich Harwood in a free speaker series event on November 11th at 6:30pm at Hood College. Harwood, the President and Founder of The Harwood Institute, will offer insights to the public in this exclusive engagement.
